# Auth-Aware UX

**Never show app-specific navigation or features to unauthenticated users.** Logged-out users should see only sign-in–related UI.

## Anti-patterns (avoid)

- Sidebar nav (Dashboard, Calendar, Help, Courses, etc.) when user is not signed in
- Search, settings, or other app features in header for logged-out users
- Links or buttons that require auth but are visible before login

## Correct pattern

- Use a **minimal layout** for unauthenticated users: no sidebar, no app header/search
- Show only branding + sign-in form (or equivalent) until the user is authenticated
- Gate layout/layout components on `user` from `useAuth()` before rendering full app shell
